  "prompt": "Where can I update the latest FIFA squad 14 for PC offline?",
  "response": "To update the latest FIFA 14 squads for PC offline, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Download Squad Files**: Look for community-created squad updates if EA Sports hasn\u2019t released a recent official update. Websites like FIFA Master, ModdingWay, or forums dedicated to FIFA modding often have the latest squad updates available for download.\n\n2. **Install a Modding Tool**: Some tools like FIFA File Explorer or FIFA Editor Tool can help you import and manage squad files effectively.\n\n3. **Replace Squad Files**:\n   - Locate your FIFA 14 installation folder (typically found in Program Files or another designated folder).\n   - Find the **\"Game\"** folder within the FIFA 14 directory.\n   - Look for the **\"Squads\"** folder. This may depend on the modding tool you are using.\n   - Replace the existing squad file with the one you downloaded.\n\n4. **Load the Game**: Once you\u2019ve replaced the squad files, start FIFA 14. You should now see the updated squad information in the game.\n\n5. **Check Community Forums**: For specific instructions and troubleshooting, check online communities or forums that focus on FIFA modding. They often provide step-by-step guides and assistance for newer users.\n\nMake sure to back up your original files before making any modifications to avoid losing your progress or the original game state.",
